{{Infobox pro wrestling championship |championshipname=NWA Anarchy Television Championship |image= |caption= |currentholder= |won= |promotion=NWA Anarchy |created=June 4, 2005 |mostreigns=Billy Buck (4 times) |firstchamp=Jeff Lewis |longestreign=Truitt Fields (567 days) |shortestreign=Tommy Penirelli (1 day) |oldest= |retired=November 14, 2015 }}
The '''NWA Anarchy Television Championship''' is a professional wrestling championship in NWA Anarchy. The title came with a stipulation that, except on occasion, it could only be defended on television.
The title was created in 2005 after [[NWA Wildside]] folded. It was created in a 4-man tournament final to unify the Georgia Junior Heavyweight and NWA Wildside Television Titles.
The title is often defended in matches with a time limit of ten or fifteen minutes. More often than with other championships, title matches result in time limit draws and the champion retaining the belt.<ref name="Television Title">{{cite web|url=http://www.nwaanarchy.com|title=NWA Anarchy Television Championship|publisher=NWA Aanarchy|accessdate=2009-05-29|date=April 18, 2009}}</ref>
